    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-01-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-01-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="546"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2"
                            type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d546fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London,
                        via Navy channels.</note>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">operational priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-01-14">14 January
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 441, personal and secret, from the President for the <gloss
                        target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Your 536.<note n="2" xml:id="d546fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_865">p. 865</ref>.</note> It
                    is my understanding that in Teheran <gloss target="#t_UJ1">U. J.</gloss> was
                    given a promise that <gloss target="#t_Overlord1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Overlord</hi>
                    </gloss> be launched during May and supported by strongest practicable <gloss
                        target="#t_Anvil1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Anvil</hi>
                    </gloss> at about the same time and that he agreed to plan for simultaneous
                    Russian attack on Eastern front.<note n="3" xml:id="d546fn3">See <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_576">pp. 576</ref>–<ref
                            target="#pg_577">577</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
